                <head>No. 543.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-01-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 4, 1874</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Official Gazette this morning contains announcement of a ministry in which
                    Marshal Serrano names himself president of the executive power of the Republic,
                    and appoints Sagasta minister of state and of the treasury, Balaguer ultramar
                    and public works, Garcia Ruiz interior and grace and justice, Admiral Topete
                    minister of marine. Balaguer, who is in charge of the colonies, held that office
                    under Sagasta in seventy-one and two.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SICKLES.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
